# Git Commit Guidelines

Every completed feature or logical unit of work MUST end with a git commit following this format.

## Format

```plaintext
<type>: <subject>

<body>
```

- **type**: feat | fix | docs | style | refactor | test | chore | ci | build | revert | perf
- **subject**: brief description in Chinese, imperative mood, no period at end
- **body**: optional detailed explanation (what and why)

## Type selection

| Type | When to use |
|------|-------------|
| `feat` | New screen, widget, route, or user-facing capability |
| `fix` | Bug fix |
| `docs` | AGENTS.md, rules, README, comments-only changes |
| `style` | Formatting only, no logic change |
| `refactor` | Restructure without changing behavior |
| `test` | Add or update tests |
| `chore` | Dependencies, tooling, project scaffolding |
| `build` | pubspec, build config changes |
| `perf` | Performance optimization |

## Flutter project examples

```plaintext
feat: 实现 Splash 启动页

根据 Figma 515:1416 还原深色背景与 Logo 居中布局。
```

```plaintext
feat: 添加设计 Token 与主题配置

在 lib/core/theme/ 中定义 AppColors、AppTextStyles 与 AppTheme。
```

```plaintext
chore: 添加 go_router 与 google_fonts 依赖
```

## Rules

- One logical feature per commit; do not mix unrelated changes.
- Run `flutter analyze` before committing feature code.
- Write subject in Chinese; keep it under 72 characters.
- Use body when the change needs context (Figma node ID, design decision).